  "body": "I have included hardhat as a dependency in an npm node module with `npm i hardhat`, but when I run `npm pack` I get the following errors:\n\n```bash\n$ npm pack\nnpm ERR! code 2\nnpm ERR! path /Users/noodle/git/NoodleOfDeath/eznft\nnpm ERR! command failed\nnpm ERR! command sh -c npm run build\nnpm ERR! > eznft@0.0.5-pre-release-package-fix build\nnpm ERR! > rimraf dist && tsc -p tsconfig.build.json\nnpm ERR! \nnpm ERR! node_modules/@ethersproject/bignumber/src.ts/bignu\nmber.ts(300,32): error TS2749: 'BN' refers to a value, but \nis being used as a type here. Did you mean 'typeof BN'?\nnpm ERR! node_modules/@ethersproject/bignumber/src.ts/bignu\nmber.ts(342,29): error TS2749: 'BN' refers to a value, but \nis being used as a type here. Did you mean 'typeof BN'?\nnpm ERR! node_modules/@ethersproject/bignumber/src.ts/bignu\nmber.ts(346,37): error TS2749: 'BN' refers to a value, but \nis being used as a type here. Did you mean 'typeof BN'?\n```\n\nHow do I go about fixing this? Do I need to downgrade hardhat?\n\nHere is my `tsconfig.json`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"lib\": [\"es7\", \"dom\"],\n    \"declaration\": true,\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true,\n    \"module\": \"commonjs\",\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"node\",\n    \"noImplicitAny\": false,\n    \"removeComments\": true,\n    \"noLib\": false,\n    \"allowSyntheticDefaultImports\": true,\n    \"emitDecoratorMetadata\": true,\n    \"experimentalDecorators\": true,\n    \"target\": \"ES2017\",\n    \"sourceMap\": true,\n    \"outDir\": \"./dist\",\n    \"baseUrl\": \"./\",\n    \"allowJs\": false,\n    \"resolveJsonModule\": true,\n    \"noUnusedLocals\": true\n  }\n}\n```\n\nand my `tsconfig.build.json`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"extends\": \"./tsconfig.json\",\n  \"include\": [\"src/**/*.ts\"],\n  \"exclude\": [\"node_modules\", \"tests\"]\n}\n```",
